result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) and Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs) was dismissed by the court.

  • Clifford D. Jamison Jr. was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Fine/costs $4611.00 reduced under the IDIP Program to $1769.00.

Serve 275 days in the Pepin County Jail commencing immediately.  Under the IDIP Program, defendant to serve 90 days with 185 days stayed under the IDIP Program.  After serving the first 48 hours without release, huber granted for employment, assessment or treatment program, and no more than 8 hours for every 2 weeks for placement with his children.
Operating privileges revoked for a period of 36 months.  Under the IDIP Program, operating privileges revoked for 24 months with 12 months stayed.
Submit to and comply with an alcohol assessment by the approved public treatment facility and comply with the development of a driver safety plan.  Referred to Arbor Place.

Defendant found IDIP eligible.  Failure to comply with the IDIP program will result in all stays of the sentence to be lifted.
AMENDED 11-30-2015:  Defendant successfully completed the IDIP program.
